%N A397055 Consider the Hilbert curve with its cells numbered starting at 0. Two players take turns and place knights at the smallest unoccupied cell not attacked by an existing knight of the other player; a(n) = k if the n-th cell has been occupied at the k-th turn, a(n) = 0 otherwise.
%H A397055 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A397055/b397055.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%H A397055 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A397055/a397055.gp.txt">PARI program</a>
%F A397055 a(A397052(k)) = 2*k - 1.
%F A397055 a(A397053(k)) = 2*k.
%F A397055 a(A397054(k)) = 0.
%e A397055 The first terms alongside the Hilbert curve are:
%e A397055     40---0  32--33--31  29--28--26
%e A397055          |   |       |   |       |
%e A397055     38--39   0--35  30---0   0--27
%e A397055      |           |           |
%e A397055     36   0---0   0  23---0   0--24
%e A397055      |   |   |   |   |   |       |
%e A397055     37---0   0--34  21   0--25--22
%e A397055                      |
%e A397055      5---8   0---9  19   0---0--20
%e A397055      |   |   |   |   |   |       |
%e A397055      6   7---0   0   0---0   0--17
%e A397055      |           |           |
%e A397055      4---3   0---0  13---0  18--16
%e A397055          |   |       |   |       |
%e A397055      1---2   0--11--10  12--15--14
